&lt;p&gt;For more source lists, see &lt;a href="https://m3u.ibert.me"&gt;https://m3u.ibert.me&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Using Cloudflare to Build gh-proxy for GitHub Acceleration</title><link>https://blog.margrop.net/en/post/cloudflare-accelerate-github-speed/</link><pubDate>Mon, 10 Jun 2024 15:26:32 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://blog.margrop.net/en/post/cloudflare-accelerate-github-speed/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;In previous episodes, I&amp;rsquo;ve experimented with Qinglong Panel. However, when trying to pull GitHub repositories, you may encounter network issues leading to pull failures. Regular GitHub file downloads are also extremely slow. So I used the free Cloudflare to build gh-proxy for GitHub acceleration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I. Prerequisites&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You need to prepare a Cloudflare account and a domain name (optional) in advance. For free domains, you can refer to the previous article &amp;lsquo;&lt;a href="http://mp.weixin.qq.com/s?__biz=MzIxMjE1NDQxNA==&amp;amp;mid=2247483945&amp;amp;idx=1&amp;amp;sn=abe651003c71d37c25b29cd6ea54a775&amp;amp;chksm=974b2368a03caa7e8ccdab8d0d104076540990a643731bd60bb9c3bbb04dc81c83dba4eedad9&amp;amp;scene=21#wechat_redirect"&gt;免费申请注册eu.org二级域名&lt;/a&gt;&amp;rsquo;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Enable Version Control for Node-RED Flows</title><link>https://blog.margrop.net/en/post/node-red-enable-version-control/</link><pubDate>Sat, 28 Aug 2021 14:40:50 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://blog.margrop.net/en/post/node-red-enable-version-control/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="problem-description"&gt;Problem Description&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I used to back up Node-RED flows by copying &lt;code&gt;~/.node-red/flows_xxx.json&lt;/code&gt; and keeping multiple versions. That was annoying, and even comparing unformatted JSON with tools like Beyond Compare was a mess.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 id="solution-pretty-print-json"&gt;Solution: Pretty-Print JSON&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I found that by changing the setting in &lt;code&gt;~/.node-red/settings.js&lt;/code&gt;, the &lt;code&gt;flows_xxx.json&lt;/code&gt; file can be saved in a pretty-printed format.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>HomeAssistant: Common HACS, Github Third-party Support Library Repos</title><link>https://blog.margrop.net/en/post/homeassistant-github-support-repo/</link><pubDate>Mon, 15 Mar 2021 08:56:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://blog.margrop.net/en/post/homeassistant-github-support-repo/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="hacs"&gt;HACS&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HACS Official Website&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/hacs/integration"&gt;https://github.com/hacs/integration&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a href="https://hacs.xyz/"&gt;https://hacs.xyz/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HACS Installation Documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://hacs.xyz/docs/installation/installation"&gt;https://hacs.xyz/docs/installation/installation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;</description></item><item><title>How to Build an Open Source Web Flowchart Tool Diagrams.net (formerly draw.io)</title><link>https://blog.margrop.net/en/post/how-to-install-docker-drawio/</link><pubDate>Sat, 30 Jan 2021 17:59:08 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://blog.margrop.net/en/post/how-to-install-docker-drawio/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;ProcessOn&lt;/code&gt; are now well-known web &lt;code&gt;流程图&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;UML&lt;/code&gt; drawing tools. However, &lt;code&gt;ProcessOn&lt;/code&gt; is a paid service with too many free-tier restrictions. So, is there a free option available?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yes, it&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;Diagrams.net&lt;/code&gt;. &lt;strong&gt;Completely free with powerful features~&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Ubuntu installs Frp server, non-client</title><link>https://blog.margrop.net/en/post/ubuntu-install-frp-server/</link><pubDate>Sat, 23 Jan 2021 13:43:20 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://blog.margrop.net/en/post/ubuntu-install-frp-server/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="download-and-extract-frp"&gt;Download and extract FRP&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Latest FRP release: &lt;a href="https://github.com/fatedier/frp/releases/"&gt;https://github.com/fatedier/frp/releases/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;cd ~
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mkdir frp
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;cd frp
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;wget https://github.com/fatedier/frp/releases/download/v0.35.0/frp_0.35.0_linux_amd64.tar.gz
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;tar -xvzf frp_0.35.0_linux_amd64.tar.gz
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;cd frp_0.35.0_linux_amd64
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1 id="configure-frp"&gt;Configure FRP&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Remove the default client configuration file&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create the server configuration file&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;cd ~/frp/frp_0.35.0_linux_amd64/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;rm frpc
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;rm frpc.ini
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;rm frpc_full.ini
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ls -a
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo su
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;rm frps.ini
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;cat&amp;gt;/etc/frps.ini&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;EOF
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;[common]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;# FRP server bind port
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;bind_port = 1000
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;# Set the HTTP access port to 1001
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;vhost_http_port = 1001
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;# Set the domain name (make sure it is reachable)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;subdomain_host = frp.margrop.net
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;# Configure the dashboard (optional)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;dashboard_port = 3456
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;# Dashboard username and password, both default to `admin`
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;dashboard_user = admin
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;dashboard_pwd = admin
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;EOF&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1 id="start-the-frp-server"&gt;Start the FRP server&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1 id="set-the-frp-server-to-start-automatically"&gt;Set the FRP server to start automatically&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Configuration file link&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Proxy Only for GitHub git clone</title><link>https://blog.margrop.net/en/post/github-git-clone-speed-up/</link><pubDate>Sun, 17 Jan 2021 12:53:12 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://blog.margrop.net/en/post/github-git-clone-speed-up/</guid><description>&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git config --global http.https://github.com.proxy socks5://127.0.0.1:1080
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git config --global https.https://github.com.proxy socks5://127.0.0.1:1080
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>